In this press briefing, Deputy Press Secretary Bill Burton provides information about President Obama's trip to Maine and Boston. The President will be greeted by various officials upon his arrival in Maine and will be introduced by Karen Mills, the head of the Small Business Administration, at his speech. In Boston, the President will be greeted by Lilly Ledbetter and will attend events with the DNC. The briefing also touches on topics such as China's attendance at a nuclear conference, the decision on warrantless wiretapping, the President's post-bill signing trips to promote the benefits of the bill, and the timing of the drilling announcement. Burton also addresses Karzai's comments about foreign involvement in the Afghan election and China's involvement in UN talks on Iran sanctions. He concludes by mentioning that Senators Snowe and Collins were invited to the event in Portland, but will not be attending.